                        <mrow>\amp=\frac{\substitute{30}-\substitute{150}}{\substitute{0}-\substitute{(-3)}}</mrow>
                        <mrow>\amp=\frac{-120}{3}</mrow>
                        <mrow>\amp=-40</mrow>
                    </md></p>
                    <p>Now we can write <m>y=-40x+b</m> and to find <m>b</m> we need look no further than one of the given points: <m>(0,30)</m>. Since the <m>x</m>-value is <m>0</m>, the value of <m>b</m> must be <m>30</m>. So, the slope-intercept form of the line is <me>y=-40x+30</me></p>
